  "soap_summary": "26-year-old female with 3-day history of a severe, progressive headache (rated 8/10), diffuse but mainly around the right eye, dull with intermittent sharper episodes. Associated symptoms: photophobia/light sensitivity, flashing lights/visual disturbances, and nausea without vomiting. No neck stiffness, no focal weakness, no speech difficulty, no recent head injury, no fever or rash. Patient tried ibuprofen (several tablets over the last two days, three tablets at a time) without relief. Family history of migraines; clinician considers a migraine-like headache (unconfirmed) and discussed stronger analgesics (naproxen, paracetamol, codeine) and prescribing today, with follow-up in 1\u20132 weeks and return precautions for vision change, focal weakness, or worsening symptoms.",
